dismissalComment.html: lazy running for the third run gets Tharanga finally. Punched away through the covers, doesn't reach the fence, Kohli gives the chase, fumbles, and then lets rip a throw on the top of the stumps to find him short. Tharanga, who has ambled the first two runs, is surprised that the throw came to his end. Almost Indian running

commentTextItems.html: game over as they pinch a single to square leg

commentPostTextItems.html: Thanks a lot for joining us, okay bye

Rohit Sharma is the MoM He says, "Always nice getting hundreds in consecutive matches. it's not the end of the world for me, I have a long way to go. Boys played really well, right from the start. This wicket was really nice to bat on, still a bit on the slower side. We knew if we got one big partnership, we would get the target."

Suresh Raina "We bowled really well, and Rohit Sharma is the man, he batted really well. I forgot, I thought I had told the umpire about the Powerplay, but he said I hadn't. Anyway we bowled really well, and Rohit and Virat batted really well too."

Tillakaratne Dilshan "We had to bowl in the right areas, we needed to take half chances because we had only 240, but it went wrong with the bat, couple of run-outs and then untimely wickets. I tried to bring the fielders up to prevent easy singles, but there was nothing in the wicket."

High fives in the Indian dressing room, this has been a remarkable comeback after having been beaten by Zimbabwe. The tri-series is wide open now. And Sharma and Kohli played beautifully after the bowling unit was very disciplined. Do stay back for the presentation

commentTextItems.html: looks to run this down to third man and is beaten
back of a length, punched away between mid-off and extra cover for four

that's it, back-to-back hundreds! Relief on Sharma's face! And then a big laugh, looks up the skies, acknowledges the standing ovation from the team balcony, hugs Raina, and then removes his helmet and raises his arms. And top shot to get there too, making room and cutting him off the stumps for four

recentReportStory.title: Rohit's second ton seals comfortable win
recentReportStory.subTitle: India v Sri Lanka, Tri-series, 2nd ODI, Bulawayo
recentReportStory.seoTitle: Rohit's second ton seals comfortable win
recentReportStory.summary: Virat Kohli played a matured hand and Rohit Sharma overcame moments of rashness to hit a delightful hundred as the pair sparkled in a 154-run partnership to charge India to a facile win
